<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>PIDEC Stage 1 Proposal Template</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Aptos, Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;
        color: #2a003b;
        line-height: 1.55;
        margin: 48px;
      }
      h1 {
        color: #2a003b;
        font-size: 28px;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      h2 {
        color: #ff5500;
        font-size: 17px;
        margin-top: 28px;
      }
      .meta {
        border: 1px solid #e5d8ec;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 16px;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      .hint {
        color: #6f4c80;
        font-size: 13px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>PIDEC 1.0 Stage 1 Proposal</h1>
    <p><strong>Theme:</strong> Engineering for Impact: Building Inclusive Solutions for a Sustainable Future</p>

    <div class="meta">
      <p><strong>Team Name:</strong></p>
      <p><strong>Department:</strong></p>
      <p><strong>Team Leader:</strong></p>
      <p><strong>Team Members:</strong></p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Problem Statement</h2>
    <p class="hint">Describe the practical problem your team wants to solve, who it affects, and why it matters.</p>
    <p></p>

    <h2>2. Proposed Engineering Solution</h2>
    <p class="hint">Explain your proposed solution, the engineering approach, core components, and how it works.</p>
    <p></p>

    <h2>3. Theme Alignment</h2>
    <p class="hint">Show how your solution supports impact, inclusion, sustainability, and real world usefulness.</p>
    <p></p>

    <h2>4. Preliminary Feasibility Assessment</h2>
    <p class="hint">Outline materials, tools, skills, build process, risks, and how your team can prototype it.</p>
    <p></p>

    <h2>5. Departmental Relevance</h2>
    <p class="hint">Explain how the proposal is grounded in your department's engineering discipline.</p>
    <p></p>

    <h2>6. Team Declaration</h2>
    <p>We confirm that this proposal is our team's original work, that no external party authored any portion of it, and that we have read and agree to the PIDEC 1.0 rules.</p>
  </body>
</html>
